<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1270376-any-thoughts-as-to-why-o-farrell-included">Any thoughts as to why O&#39;Farrell included the - almost but not really - incest story between Alex and Iris? Was the Author saying - all families have secrets don&#39;t judge (or incarcerate)? Or (when Kitty caught them at it) Iris IS the bloodline of Esme because just look at how she conducts herself?
Any ideas greatly received.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1270376'><a id="like_count_community_question_1270376" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1270376?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F250729.The_Vanishing_Act_of_Esme_Lennox">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1270376-any-thoughts-as-to-why-o-farrell-included">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1270376-any-thoughts-as-to-why-o-farrell-included">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
