  <span id="freeText17348790248948215402" style="display:none">[4.5] This haunting novel leaves most of Esme’s life to the reader’s imagination. For me that made her story even more powerful and sad. And infuriating - I was so angry with her family. O’Farrell brilliantly meshes the narratives of Iris, Kitty and Esme in a way that keeps illuminating and moving the novel forward. And the ending is quite fascinating...and hopeful too. I love that Iris doesn't let go. </span>
