<div id="review_3734674575" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3734674575" />
    <a title="fleurette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4692637-fleurette"><img alt="fleurette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1357165343p2/4692637.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3734674575?book_show_action=true">Jan 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="fleurette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="fleurette" href="/user/show/4692637-fleurette">fleurette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4692637-fleurette?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3734674575" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12383361341907293315">It is a book rather outside of what I usually read. I also expected something different. And while I enjoyed many parts of this story, it still isn&apos;t a book for me. That&apos;s why it&apos;s hard for me to review it or rate. <br/><br/>I expected a crime story. Meanwhile, it is a fiction or a women’s fiction. There is a small thread related to the mystery, but for most of the book we don&apos;t even know that there is some mystery we can wait for. Women’s fiction is not a genre that I particularly like or read often. But</span>
  <span id="freeText12383361341907293315" style="display:none">It is a book rather outside of what I usually read. I also expected something different. And while I enjoyed many parts of this story, it still isn't a book for me. That's why it's hard for me to review it or rate. <br /><br />I expected a crime story. Meanwhile, it is a fiction or a women’s fiction. There is a small thread related to the mystery, but for most of the book we don't even know that there is some mystery we can wait for. Women’s fiction is not a genre that I particularly like or read often. But as such, the story is quite nice.<br /><br />This is basically the story of three generations of Lennox women told by Kitty through the prism of her sister Esme story. If you like psychologically complicated characters and difficult family relationships, you will love this story. From Ishbel, the mother of Kitty and Esme, to the sisters to Iris, all women have something fascinating about them. We should probably also add Ishbel's mother-in-law, who also leaves her mark on Esme's life. Personally, I am not a big fan of this type of story, but that is rather my personal preference.<br /><br />Which does not change the fact that Esme's story really touched me. There is so much desperation and misunderstanding in it. At the same time, it is striking that although Esme's story is a fiction, similar things could have happened in the old days, and probably did many times. I think it was this credibility of Esme's story that struck me the most and made the greatest impression on me.<br /><br />I am glad that I read this book, because sometimes it is good to read something outside of my usual range. But I still don't think it was a story for me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12383361341907293315" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


